msgid ""
"In `RequestScopedBeanTests`, we inject both the `UserService` (that is, the "
"subject under test) and the `MockHttpServletRequest` into our test "
"instance. Within our `requestScope()` test method, we set up our test "
"fixture by setting request parameters in the provided "
"`MockHttpServletRequest`. When the `loginUser()` method is invoked on our "
"`userService`, we are assured that the user service has access to the "
"request-scoped `loginAction` for the current `MockHttpServletRequest` (that "
"is, the one in which we just set parameters). We can then perform assertions "
"against the results based on the known inputs for the username and "
"password. The following listing shows how to do so:"
msgstr ""

